    "plan_content": "Here's the full plan I've researched and written up.\n\n---\n\n## Plan Summary: `ollama rename` Feature\n\nAfter reading all relevant source files, the feature requires touching exactly **4 files** with no new imports or dependencies needed anywhere.\n\n### 1. `api/types.go` — Add `RenameRequest` (after line 765)\nA struct mirroring `CopyRequest` exactly — `Source` and `Destination` string fields with `json:\"source\"` / `json:\"destination\"` tags.\n\n### 2. `api/client.go` — Add `Client.Rename` (after line 387)\nA method identical in shape to `Client.Copy`: POST to `/api/rename`, request body marshalled from `*RenameRequest`, no response body.\n\n### 3. `server/routes.go` — `RenameHandler` + route\nThe handler (inserted after `CopyHandler` at line 1483) implements the following logic:\n1. Bind JSON → 400 on bad request\n2. Parse + validate source name with `model.ParseName` → 400 on invalid\n3. **`manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)`** — 404 if `os.IsNotExist`, saves `srcManifest` for later\n4. Parse + validate destination name the same way → 400 on invalid\n5. **`manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)`** — if it *succeeds* (no error) → **409 Conflict**\n6. `CopyModel(src, dst)` to copy the manifest file (layers are shared content-addressed blobs)\n7. `srcManifest.Remove()` — removes only the source manifest file, **not** `RemoveLayers()` (destination now owns the same layers)\n\nRoute added on line 1699: `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)`\n\n### 4. `cmd/cmd.go` — CLI `RenameHandler` func + `renameCmd` cobra command\n- `RenameHandler` mirrors `CopyHandler`: calls `client.Rename(...)`, prints `renamed 'X' to 'Y'\\n`\n- `renameCmd`: `Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\"`, `ExactArgs(2)`, `PreRunE: checkServerHeartbeat`\n- Added to the env-docs loop and `rootCmd.AddCommand`\n\n### HTTP response table\n\n| Scenario | Status |\n|---|---|\n| Bad/missing body, invalid name | 400 |\n| Source not found | **404** |\n| Destination already exists | **409** |\n| Filesystem error | 500 |\n| Success | 200 (empty body) |",
